<BaseLayout title="About — Ryan Chibana" description="About Ryan Chibana — Senior Software Engineer">
  <h1>About</h1>

  <p>
    I'm a senior software engineer based in Carmel, Indiana. I currently work at Block, where I've been building observability platforms for compliance screening workflows, optimizing Kafka-based infrastructure, and building MCP servers for LLM-driven querying. I also spend time helping other engineers learn about multi-agent development and agentic workflows.
  </p>

  <p>
    Before Block, I worked at Cruise on ML infrastructure for autonomous vehicles, and spent five years at Yelp building and scaling data pipelines that connected internal databases with Salesforce, Marketing Cloud, Braze, and Twilio Segment. Before that, I was at Epic Systems working on usage analytics for electronic health records.
  </p>

  <p>
    I started out studying Computer Science at Indiana University, where I also taught a lab section on computer structures and embedded systems. I later completed a Master's in CS at Georgia Tech with a focus on machine learning.
  </p>

